# Custom denylist: files that must NEVER be copied to any linked worktree.
# This file is a project-local extension to .worktreeinclude semantics —
# not part of the Anthropic official spec. Entries here override .worktreeinclude
# regardless of any negation (!pattern) in that file.
# Syntax: same gitignore semantics as .worktreeinclude.
.env.production
.env.staging
*.pem
*.p12
*deploy*key*
*credential*.json
*service-account*.json
# Recursion guard: .worktree-backup/ is gitignored and would otherwise be enumerated
# by `git ls-files --others --ignored`, causing nested re-copy on each worktree-start
# (issue #637). Both forms are listed for gitignore semantics: trailing-slash matches
# directories only, bareword matches both. Negation is not possible (see header).
# Note: gitignore semantics match these entries at ANY directory depth, including
# nested forms like outer/.worktree-backup/inner/.private-info-allowlist. This
# layer catches what the hardcoded loop guard in worktree-copy.js intentionally
# does not — the guard is anchored at the relPath root; this denylist is not.
.worktree-backup/
.worktree-backup
